Description: Lakeland's most arresting flowers right in your own home.
Name: Lakeland Flower Garden

Description: A metallic idol forged in the likeness of the Ruby Weapon.
Name: Ruby Totem

Description:
A winged helmet forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse.

Two helms can be traded for special headgear.
Name: Helm of Golden Antiquity

Singular: suit of armor of golden antiquity
Plural: suits of armor of golden antiquity
Description:
Emblazoned armor forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse.

Four suits can be traded for special body gear.
Name: Armor of Golden Antiquity

Singular: pair of gauntlets of golden antiquity
Plural: pairs of gauntlets of golden antiquity
Description:
Wrought-iron gauntlets forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse.

Two pairs can be traded for special arm gear.
Name: Gauntlets of Golden Antiquity

Singular: pair of chausses of golden antiquity
Plural: pairs of chausses of golden antiquity
Description:
Heavy chausses forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse.

Four pairs can be traded for special leg gear.
Name: Chausses of Golden Antiquity

Singular: pair of greaves of golden antiquity
Plural: pairs of greaves of golden antiquity
Description:
Tarnished greaves forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse.

Two pairs can be traded for special foot gear.
Name: Greaves of Golden Antiquity

Description: An ornamented belt created by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse. Alas, advancements in trouser technology have rendered it worthless.
Name: Belt of Golden Antiquity

Description:
An extravagant bangle forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse.

One bangle can be traded for a special accessory.
Name: Bangle of Golden Antiquity

Description:
A short apocryphal tome presumably created by Eden for recordkeeping purposes.

Copies of the same Eden's Verse apocrypha can be traded for special gear.
Name: Book of Fulmination

Description:
A short apocryphal tome presumably created by Eden for recordkeeping purposes.

Copies of the same Eden's Verse apocrypha can be traded for special gear.
Name: Book of Furor

Name: Book of Iconoclasm

Description:
A short apocryphal tome presumably created by Eden for recordkeeping purposes.

Copies of the same Eden's Verse apocrypha can be traded for special gear.
Name: Book of Refulgence

Description: A golden blade forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse. Though such weapons were once considered highly valuable, demand has dried up and they are now essentially worthless.
Name: Blade of Golden Antiquity

Description: A sparkling substance produced by the artisans of the Crystalline Mean, used─when resources permit─to enhance the properties of Crystarium weapons such as those used by the guard. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.
Name: Crystalline Ester

Description: A sparkling thread produced by the artisans of the Crystalline Mean, used─when resources permit─to augment Crystarium vestments such as those used by the guard. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.
Name: Crystalline Twine

Description: A sparkling coating produced by the artisans of the Crystalline Mean, used─when resources permit─to strengthen Crystarium accessories such as those used by the guard. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.
Name: Crystalline Glaze

Description: A note of promise received from Mowen for the delivery of Allagan tomestones of allegory. However, due to the House of Splendors changing its policies, it is now worth less than the paper on which it is scribed.
Name: Mowen's Token (Allegory)

Description: A rare and beautiful tomestone made of nigh-indestructible fused quartz. This particular variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.
Name: Perdurable Tomestone
